properties.description: Graphic. Witness. #BasharCrimes #Syria 15 year old child tortured to death: http://t.co/55WGjRz7

A real fear on the life of the detainee dentist Maad Tayeh:

In a new crime, the Syrian government made up a fire accident and they
burned the house of the detainee dentist Maad Tayeh while his family
is inside the house. His four children were killed: The oldest one is
nine years old, and the youngest is 10 months, while the mother was
survived as a miracle.

The dentist, Maad Tyeh, was arrested on September,10th, 2011 and he is
currently in the military Saidnaya prison. His family is fearing the
worst to happen to the dentist Maad Tayeh by the violent Syrian
regime.

In the attachment, one can see a mourning paper for three of the children:
Ezaldeen Maad Tayeh, 9 years old
Essa Maad Tayeh, 3 years old
Hamzeh Maad Tayeh, 10 months.

properties.description:
*Statement of Jasem city coordinating on the crimes of Captain Amer Ahmed
and others: *

The captain in the army, Amer Ahmed, known as Abu Hydra, is still
exercising the most heinous of crimes against our people in Jasem city
several months ago, like threatening and intimidating, and  abusing
activists and their families, and even murdering people in cold blood.

One of the activist got  Amer Ahmed's  phone number recently and he called
him to say: " You are responsible of the killing of four martyrs in Jasem"
The captain Amer Ahmed said: " I hope I am responsible of killing fifty
thousands people not just four." He is referring to the population of the
city of Jasem, and he wanted to show his willingness to continue his crimes.

The Captain Amer Ahmad, shot the martyr Osama Aljlm in the middle of
Freedom Square in Jasem on October, 20th, 2011. Also, Eid Husain Alhaj was
arrested by the patrol led by Captain Ahmed Amer on November, 12th, 2011.
After a couple of hours of his arrest, Eid Husain Alhaj was found
slaughtered by a spear of a rifle and his body was lying behind his house. In
the same way, Sami Alhari was arrested on Abu Tammam roundabout on
November, 12th, 2011 and after two hours his body was handed over to his
family.

In addition to that Amer Ahmad continue to threat and intimidate the people
and to conduct raids of arrest. He also continues in threatening the
detainees' families that he will return their kids dead. He is responsible
also about arresting family members as hostages of wanted activists.

We, activists in Jassem coordinating, demand the inclusion of the name of
Captain Amer Ahmad in the sanction lists of the international community of
members of the Syrian regime  to hold them accountable and prosecuted after
the fall of the regime. Note that we are ready to provide the necessary
documents to prove this criminal convictions and practices against the
people of Jassem.

You can collect signatures of many Syrian citizens in the city of Jassem
which condemns this butcher along with many of his colleagues who are
involved in the killings, repression and torture, including:

1- Lieutenant General Moataz Wardeh, who is from Sahl Algab and he is on
the checkpoint of Nimr road.
2-  Colonel  Youssef Ismail (Yousif Asfour), who is responsible about
Alsaha (Square) massacre. 3- Lieutenant General Hossam Khaddour of brigade
43
4- Colonel Ali Shaaban
5- Colonel Ali Younes
6- Colonel Abdullah Al-Zeer, who is from Homs, Wa'ar neighborhood.
7- Lieutenant General Osama Allwaa, from brigade 43 and he is on Jabieh
checkpoint.
8- Sergeant Musab al-Ali, who is from Homs
9- Lieutenant Imad Asad ,who is from Lattakia
10- Recruiter Mohammed AlHalabi
11- Lieutenant General Mohammad AlMeer, who is in the hospital checkpoint.
12- Assistant officer, Mohammed Hassan AlSaleh (Arsan), from Jassem
13- Recruiter Omar Mohammed Saeed Azzam
14- Brigade commander Younis Okdeh, the commander of the ninth division.
15- General Hassan Merhej, who is from Lattakia
16- Major General Mohammad Musa Alkhairat (Ghazawi), the commander of the

properties.description:
Urgent Action about the detainee Mohammad Anwar Lutfi Aldabbas: Mohammad Anwar Lutfi Aldabbas was arrested from the national hospital in Daryya, Damascus County on January, 1st, 2012. Mohammad is a peaceful
activist and he participated in many demonstrations in Daryya, Damascus
County before. The last one was on Sunday January, 1st, 2011 when he was
shot by the air force security at his back and the bullet stayed in his
lung.

Mohammad was in the national hospital and he was in the operation room
under anesthesia when a group of the air force security men raided the
hospital and they kidnapped him. Mohammad Aldabbas is in a  critical health
situation right now and he is under big risk of receiving bad treatment, being tortured and maybe killed.

While we held the Syrian regime accountable of any harm may affect Mohammad
Aldabbas, we would like to mention that Mohammad's brother in law Ghiath
Matar was killed in custody on September, 10th, 2011  in the air force
security branch after his arrest on September, 6th, 2011 and he was
tortured to death.

As of the 10th of September 2011, a young doctor, Maad Mohammad Mawaheb
Tayeh, was arrested while in his clinic in the city of Latakia, Syria.

Dr. Maad subsequently was not released until now, and he was left without
specific condemning accusations, which contradicts not only norms and laws
including the Syrian Constitution, but also to all human rights.

Current news report that the young dentist, and the father of four
children, will be converted to the military field court which is even a new
violation to the norms and customary laws of the Syrian Constitution,
because of him being a civilian. In addition, his seizure forms a clear
paradox with the suspension of the State of Emergency and the Martial Law,
as stated by official authorities in Syria several months ago, knowing that
false charges are issued against many detainees converting them to field
military courts for malevolent purposes after clutching different
confessions from them under implausible cruel torture. Latest news acquired
is that Maad was visited by relatives at the 28th of December, 2011 in
Sydnaya prison near Damascus, where implications of torture were
significant.

 He also showed his suffering from starvation, showing that he lost about
60% of his weight. It was also discovered that Dr. Maad was presented to
field military court on the 22nd of December, 2011, where all charges
fabricated against him were denied by him.

 In the 3rd of January, 2012, Dr. Maad was visited again, and he was
presented to the same court again, but the details were not identified
since the detainee is not allowed any representation or defense, or a
lawyer in these types of court, hence Dr. Maad can be sentenced to
execution because of the false accusations by this regime, and because no
lawyer can represent him in this case.

INFORMATION CONCERNING DR. MAAD:
Family name: TAYEH
Given name: MAAD
Sex: Male
Occupation/profession: Dentist
Father

The story of a Syrian martyr by his relative. ||      

*The story of a Syrian martyr by his relative*
*
*
Mohammad Alfakeer was born in 1990 in Gabagb, Daraa . His father is Radwan
Alfakeer and his mother is Fatemah Alahmad and he has three sisters and a
younger brother who is suffering from diabetes and he is in bad shape.
Mohammad dreamed of freedom, future and stability. Mohammad was getting
married on December, 30th, 2011. Mohammad works in gas station.

Mohammad participated in a demonstration on Friday December, 23rd, 2011 in
Gabagb, Daraa province where he is from. The military security accompanied
by while Toyota cars  fired directly at the demonstrators. Mohammad was
shot in his leg which prevented him from running and the military security
instead of taking him to the hospital, they execute him by shooting his
head while he was lying on the ground.  Mohammad was killed in a cold blood
with another demonstrator and four others were injured during Gabagb's
demonstration.

The suffering of Mohammad Alfakeer's family did not finish by his death
since the military security threatened his family that they will take his
body which led his father to bury him at night and quickly with a few of
his relatives participated in his funeral.

properties.description:
*An Appeal from the people in Jabl Alzawieh, Idlib: *

To all the honest people and leaders in the world. We call on all human
rights organizations and international humanitarian agencies, the Arab
Ministerial Council, the UN Security Council and the High Commissioner of
Human Rights, the Secretary General of the United Nations to speed up in
rescuing us from the death policy that is pursued by the Syrian army
and barbaric
Alshabiha. The Syrian army is committing massacre against the civilians in
Jabl Alzawieh, Idlib where they destroy the civilians' houses, mosques,
hospitals  and they are using different kind of military weapons from tanks
and anti-aircraft heavt machines. The humanitarian responsibility is upon
you.
Signature
The people who remain in Jabl Alzawieh, Idlib
December, 20th, 2011

       ....      
 ...        
          
          
            
             
           
  .....          ...

properties.incident: More Than 110 people are killed in Idlib, Syria only today on December, 20th, 2011.
properties.incident translation: More Than 110 people are killed in Idlib, Syria only today on December, 20th, 2011.
properties.description:
*Idlib, Syria || December, 20th, 2011 *

We have documented by name
53 names of the martyrs (the majority of them are civilians )

After the Syrian military, the security forces and Alshabiha raided most of
the villages and the towns of jabl Alzawieh using tens of the heavy weapons
like tanks and military trucks. Many of the activists were fled to a jungle
area west of Kokfeen which is next to Kafr Awaid and the Syrian army
started shooting without stop at the activists for 5 hours continuously and
shelling the area using tanks. Many women tried to break the besiege on the
activists but they were not successful. The Syrian military raided almost
all the villages in the area of Jabl Alzawieh, Idlib and they arrested many
guys from the village of Kafr Awaid and they executed them immediately and
that happened while many of the activists from all the villages take a
refugee in the area.

The corpses were gathered in the northern mosque in Kafr Awaid  while the
Syrian army are threatening to attack the mosque in any moment. Activists
were able to count more than 110 bodies in northern Kafr Awaid mosque and
more than 11 bodies in Almozra mosque.  The massacre left tens of wounded
people as well.

So far we were able to identify 53 names of the martyrs who were killed by
the Syrian military only today in December, 20th, 2011 from Kafr Awaid,
Kansfra, Serjeh in addition to many more wounded.  *Kafr Awaid massacre in Jab Alzawieh, Idlib || December, 20th, 2011 *

While the shelling on many of the villages of Jabl Alzawieh is still
undergoing until this moment by tank shells and anti-aircraft bullets, for
example: Kafr Awaid, Kansfra, Alftaira, Almozra, and Kokfeen. The
electricity are cut off on most of Idlib areas.

properties.description:
Homs: Summary of Events, Monday, November 7, 2011

Eid night...spent listening to the song of gunfire sung by Bashar
Homs spent the first night of Eid listening to the sound of gunfire, sound
bombs to terrorize people, and real bombs too. In each of Bab Tadmur, Bab
Al-Draib, Bab Al-Sbaa, and Al-Mrejeh glass shattered from the bombs and
residents saw burning cars in the streets in the morning as if getting
revenge from the residents.  Here are some videos that show some of the
destruction:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2qU3UnJ70g0
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_LNbvLCG5kw
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JVi3r7CcgDY
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZiLYp1FFET4
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4ztNER4CujU

Baba Amr remains under siege and bullets being shot at residents, not to
mention the rockets that can't be explained with anything other than pure
hatred directed at those seeking freedom and justive. Most stores have been
looted in the middle of the night and their contents stolen. In Deir Balba,
several people were sniped, among them one martyr, Khalid Al-Abbou and
several wounded. Reports also reached us about the death of martyr Khalid
Abdelkarim Al-Raheem, a soldier who died as a result of torture at the
Military Security branch because he refused to fire at people.
Here is a video of the aftermath of bombing in Baba Amr:
http://youtu.be/7I9K0YpbD4Y
More videos from Baba Amr from yesterday:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2FRUntYPTyU
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vm8LROjB-Pg
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T5k60IjP_vM
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xWNOEVQzVcY
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=to5KWFli-mk
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OIYCZ9xtTqY
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T0de1NPbZbI
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-ILmyPwFPak

In the morning...in Al-Holeh again
After the residents knew where they stand after the massacre on the day of
the meeting of the Arab League, the massacre committed by the regime to get
a reaction out of the area and try to damage the unity of people, today,
bombing and shooting at the area resumed using all types of weapons and
directed at residential homes. The result so far is the death of child
martyr Maymouna Al-Sayed, an 8 year old girl and the injury of several
people, among them a woman.

In Baba Amr there was a widespread and random arrest campaign that reached
any young man present in the neighborhood, after their homes were bombed
and their possessions stolen. Tanks are still in the streets of Baba Amr
and other Homs neighborhoods. Another noticeable thing around Homs today is
that by the west entrance, Tartous road, from the side of the Homs
Petrolium Refinery, there was a great number of army forces which weren't
in Homs before. It is unknown where they are there. Also, a huge number of
forces were also noted this afternoon on the southern entrance of Homs in
the direction of the Damascus road. The number of forces is estimated to be
over 5000.

Homs offered 7 confirmed martyrs on the second day of Eid, mostly the
result of sniping pedestrians and random bullets, among them a little girl
and a woman. Here are some relevant videos:

to fire at people

properties.description:
Syrian National Council &amp; Homs Committee-part of LCCS: statements
declaring the city of Homs a disaster area

Urgent call by Homs coordination committees- local coordination committees of Syria, Homs 5 - Nov - 2011
Homs province: A disaster area and a disaster stricken city:
On the 18th of March, chanting originated in the courtyard of the Khalid bin Waleed Mosque; the chants glorified freedom and were in solidarity with Daraa; its detained children and its foremost martyrs. Since then the flame of revolution did not wane in Homs, the city of 2,000,000 residents. Nor, for eight month, did the regimes retaliation stop; with its machine for killing, torture and aggravations.
More than 1,400 martyrs, 4,000 prisoners who are right now under lawless and arbitrary detention, 100s missing, and 100s of families displaced, and dozens of houses destroyed. This is the initial outcome of the regimes reaction to the steadfastness of the people of Homs confronting the regime with demands for freedom. 
Since the massacre on the 19th of April, the army entered Homss cities and towns, and had not left since. With the exception of some areas that are pro-regime, all the cities, towns, and neighborhoods of Homs, have been exposed to attacks, incursions, and massacres, including the cities of Rastan, Talbiseh, Hawla, Palmyra, and the neighborhoods of Bab Sbaa, Bab Dreib, Bab Tadmur, Bab Hood, Bayada, Khaldieh, Deir Balba, Ghouta, Inshaat, Hamra, Qusour, Qarabis, Jourat Al-Shayyah, Shammas, and other rebellious area in Homs.
Still, what is taking place, for about a week now, in the neighborhood of Baba Amr, exceeds all the crimes of the times, in cruelty and savagery. Baba Amr, a neighborhood in the southeastern part of Homs city, had scarified the largest number of martyrs in Homs until today. In the last week alone 40 of its free people fell martyrs. The residents of the neighborhood suffered incessant shelling with rockets, artillery, cannons, various types of machine guns, and heavy anti-aircraft, resulting in the destruction of dozens of homes, all the while, the neighborhood is under  a suffocating siege by security and army forces; in which security forces prevented ambulance crews from evacuating the wounded and providing treatment to them.  Food, including bread, and medical supplies vanished. Communications, electricity, drinking water, heating fuel are all cut off.  Also 100s of families fled and were displaced to face homelessness in the harsh winter; after the army, security forces, and Shabiha (regime-sponsored gangs) turned to the method of using children and civilians as human shields in  the regimes hunt down of the defected element  [defected from the regimes service] joining the Free Syrian Army.
The coordination committees in Homs; those of whom joined the local coordination committees of Syria, with sorrow and sadness announce the province of Homs a disaster area, and appeals to all those responsible for prolonging the suffering of the Syrian people, and especially the people of Homs, to act quickly and to provide support and aid.
Homs 5 - Nov - 2011
 Homs coordination committees- local coordination committees of Syria

properties.description:
Homs: Summary of events  Monday, October 17, 2011

As residents of Homs are used to now, they spend their night listening to
the sound of bullets, rockets, and explosions. Tonight was no better, as
several armored vehicles stormed Deir Balba to fire heavily and launch
rockets, hitting several homes, while power was out in the neighborhood. The
sounds of explosions and heavy machine guns were also heard in the
neighborhoods of Al-Bayada, Al-Khaldiyeh, Baba Amro, Al-Waar, Jib
Al-Jandali, Karm Al-Zeitoun, and Al-Nazeheen. The air force also roamed the
skies of the city and its suburbs terrorizing the city and the northern
villages.

Three martyrs, who were killed yesterday in Al-Inshaat by security and
Shabiha, were mourned today in Baba Amro. They are: Taher Al-Sibaai, Tamer
Mando, and Gazwan Ghalioun. Here are some videos of the funeral in Baba
Amro:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IXHFZ2Ngvuw
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9eGP_0pAeEs
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vD5mgvSdN-Y
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6YqABk_9ye4

A funeral that was being held for martyrs in Al-Khaldiyeh ended abruptly
when Assad forces opened fire at the mourners, resulting in some injuries.
Here are some videos of the funeral for Al-Khaldiyeh martyrs who were killed
yesterday when the neighborhood was being shelled during the Arab League
meeting on October 16, 2011:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QbraqbbA0Tk
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DiiqGhxKhXI
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j0-As9YabIc

Firing at mourners in Al-Khaldiyeh by security forces:
 http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GbMzsU6vq98

Armored vehicles firing in Al-Khaldiyeh during the evening demonstration,
which was also during the Arab League meeting on October 16, 2011
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SBvvEurzH4s

The death of martyrs Muhannad Al-Abdullah and Ashraf Sheikh Alsouk was
confirmed as a result of being shot yesterday by bullets from armored
vehicles and members of the Assad army while they were coming back to their
homes in Al-Khaldiyeh. The funeral of martyr Salem Tayara went out in Bab
Al-Draib, where he was killed by Assad security thugs early morning on
October 17, 2011.

Burial of martyr Muhammad Salem Tayara in Bab Al-Draib on October 17, 2011
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kf7YUMzNAMM

Wake for martyr Salem Tayara in Bab Al-Draib on October 17, 2011
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UWN_rj7UO7g

A funeral was also held for martyr Muhammad Fadi Kaada in Bab Tadmur, where
he was killed by a bullet of Assad forces.
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A-xNLoAJsRA

Students in Al-Ghouta went out in a spontaneous demonstration, which angered
Assad security forces who started firing in the air and chasing students, in
an attempt to arrest them and terrorize them:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gg3jqEYi9xE
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ykO16lQsizo

At dawn, and after the homes were combed home-by-home in the neighborhoods
of Bab Al-Sibaa, Al-Mrejeh, and Al-Khader the last two days to ensure
residents are unarmed, Assad forces armed with heavy weapons, tanks, armored
vehicles, and other weapons attacked and bombed the neighborhoods, targeting
homes and stores. Their bullets did not distinguish between young and old or
man and woman, even though they do not care about that anyway. As if killing
and destroying were not enough, Assad forces prevented ambulances from
reaching the neighborhood and the wounded. They also attacked Red Crescent
envoys and carjacked some ambulances to use them to enter the neighborhood
and arrest some of the wounded.

The bullets and bombs started at 6 am and had not stopped most day. The
number of wounded reached tens of people, most of them remained in their
homes without help, some of them bleeding to death and some (more than 30)
were arrested. Additionally, a number of martyrs fell, some known, and some
whose names were still unconfirmed. Some of the confirmed martyrs are:
Sharid Kaada, M. Abdelrahman Al-Abdah, Abdelmatlab Al-Sabbagh, Yaseen Shama,
Moayed Mahrat, Omar Abdelhasib Al-Talawi, Abeer Sheikh Al-Souk, Majd
Al-Hallak, Dawod Sulieman Al-Jasem, Jasem Afara.

After combing the neighborhoods home-by-home, using searching for weapons as
an excuse, Assad forces decided to declare a war to exterminate and destroy
most neighborhoods of Homs starting from Deir Balba, through Al-Bayada,
Al-Khaldiyeh, Juret Al-Shayah, Al-Inshaat, Baba Amro, Karm Al-Shami,
Al-Midan, and Bab Al-Draib. The operation focused on the neighborhoods of
Baba Amro, Al-Khaldiyeh, Al-Bayada, Deir Balba, Jib Al-Jandali, Karm
Al-Zeitoun, and Al-Nazeheen. There were tens of wounded as a result, who
were tended to in homes because it was impossible to take them to hospitals
or medical centers. Some martyrs from these neighborhoods were: M. Khaled
Al-Bashan (Deir Balba), Haj Fajr Ahmad Al-Dhabi, 70 years old (Jobar, near
Baba Amro), M. Abdelkader Kaada and Adnan Ghalioun, 55 years old (Jib
Al-Jnadali), M. Khaled Al-Nasser (Al-Bayada), M. Samer Mando, Muhannad
Al-Abdullah, Akram Mustapha Mando, Fadi Dabous, and Kamel Swaidan
(Al-Khaldiyeh), Sharif Kaada and Ayham Al-Beirouti (Bab Al-Draib),
Abdelmouti Hasan Sinbul (Al-Nazeheen), Mahmoud Al-Kaheel, 50 years old
(Ashira).

Random firing at homes in Baba Amro
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jidQhDDq-So
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cUlhgD5DeMk
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wlDSdKMKroY

Some of the rockets shot at homes in Al-Khaldiyeh
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5B4n_xLAp5c

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p8WSRnYGFvU

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9tWSkcAdswg

Large security and military reinforcements arrived to the town of Al-Qusayr,
which was surrounded from all entrances, amid news of defection of more than
30 soldiers at the northern entrance of town, and fire exchange there.

The village of Gharnata held a funeral for martyr Nizar Al-Taleb, 36 years
old, who died under torture in the basements of security branches, where he
was arrested about a week ago, and his body was handed over today, with
clear signs of torture.

The village of Abel also got its share of killing, raids, and destruction.
Assad forces supported by the army surrounded the village, raided homes, and
looted homes and stores, only to resume random shelling and firing in the
evening from checkpoints. Assad army members are spread around the village.

The residents of Al-Holeh went out in solidarity with Homs, in a massive
demonstration to prove that the martyrs blood will not be shed in vain, and
to relay to the Arab world and international community the message that
their silence is killing us, and apathy is increasing the number of our
victims.
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WA0DY8qhUa0

In defiance to all the weapons and silence of the world, residents of Homs
went out demonstrating and chanting in the neighborhoods of Al-Waar,
Al-Qusoor, Al-Ghouta, Al-Inshaat, Deir Balba, Al-Kaldiyeh, Al-Bayada,
Al-Shammas, Baba Amro, Juret Al-Arayes, Al-Karabees, Juret Al-Shayah,
Al-Mrejeh, Bab Houd, and others. Residents also demonstrated in other towns
and villages around Homs, like Al-Holeh, Tadmur, Al-Qusayr, and
Al-Qaryatain. Most demonstrations were attacked and fired at to be
dispersed.

As usual, the Assad forces fired rockets from tanks and machine gun fire in
the evening in neighborhoods in which it is present, especially in Deir
Balba, Al-Bayada, Karm Al-Zeitoun, Al-Naseheen (where nail bombs were used),
Bab Al-Sibaa, Al-Mrejeh, Bab Al-Draib, Baba Amro, and Al-Khaldiyeh. This was
amid news of many injuries. The Assad forces also opened fire in the town of
Al-Qusayr, directing it at streets and buildings. But there were no reports
of injuries. Assad forces also fired from checkpoints around town
(Al-Mashtal, Al-Sawameh, Al-Baladiyeh, and Al-Kaniseh).

Homs: Summary from Thursday, October 20, 2011

From the heat of Misrata Homs gets hotter!
Despite the bullets, the injuries, the arrests, the miserable conditions,
and while the residents of Homs are washing the streets with their blood,
Homs gets more medals of honor for all it is going through. The gunfire has
been going on all day in Al-Khaldiyeh, Al-Bayada, Al-Nazeheen, Al-Seteen
street, and some towns around Homs. There number of those wounded was
greatest in Heet, Sakarja, Al-Burhaniyeh, and Al-Qusayr. There are more than
20 missing and 6 confirmed martyrs today from different areas. The martyrs
are Walid Harfoush, Muhammad Deeb Othman, 3 from Al-Hameed family, and a
woman from Deir Balba. The exact numbers are difficult to confirm because of
the inability to move around or communicate. There were home raids and
arrests in Deir Balba this morning amid gunfire, and some of the
neighborhood homes were destroyed. In Karm Al-Zeitoun, explosions and
gunfire were heard all day, and in each of Bab Al-Sbaa, Bab Houd, Bab
Al-Draib, and Baba Amro, checkpoints continue on firing in and at the
neighborhoods.

The remnants of the woman killed in Deir Balba after the shelling:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lMsPJNUJD1w

Tanks in Al-Holeh today:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gpuu8UwRZew

The funeral of one of the Homs martyrs
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bg1IzDGxpeE

The Faculty of Petro-chemistry in Deir Balba is turned into a military
barrack:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rynd36gcbTs

Signs of the shelling in Deir Balba:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mCgLXFi_FYA
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NMNOKnxVxmI
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p1S1zcp-qb0

Al-Qusayr and surrounding townsfarms, homes, and residents
The Assad forces and thugs continued surrounding Al-Qusayr and some of the
surrounding towns. Today, the Assad forces raided some of the farms and
destroyed their crops, and arrested many of the residents. More than 50
armored vehicles, 30 soldier-carrying trucks, and a large number of
accompanying car are currently in Al-Qusayr. Some homes went up in flames
and others were destroyed in Al-Qusayr and surrounding towns. Some of the
Assad forces were also deployed to the towns of Al-Dabaa and Al-Bayoda
Al-Sharqiyeh. The towns are now surrounded, and with power outages and
severed communications. Conditions are very difficult, roads to the towns
are blocked, and moving within the towns is near impossible. This operation
against Al-Qusayr and surrounding towns is still going on and conditions are
miserable. In addition, reports and news are nearly impossible to obtain.

Conditions continue to be miserable in Homs, with the sounds of pain rising
above the bullets so the world may take notice. The women of Baba Amro and
other neighborhoods in Homs went out demonstrating today before its men, the
students demonstrate during the day, and the young men go out at night, all
of them asking the world to break the silence. Here are some example videos
from around Homs today.

Arab League Grace Period

A large number of martyrs and woundedand the time extension by the Arab
League continues
So far, there are 11 confirmed martyrs in all areas of the city. Baba Amro
is under rubble after Al-Jouri mosque and homes nearby were bombed. Gunfire
is still ongoing, and the true number of martyrs and wounded is still
unknown. There are 26 confirmed wounded people, some in very serious
condition. Reinforcements are still arriving in Baba Amro, and conditions
are miserable. There was also heavy gunfire in each of Bab Al-Sbaa, Bab
Al-Draib, Bab Houd, Al-Khaldiyeh, Al-Bayada, Deir Balba, Al-Ghouta, and
Al-Inshaat. Until now it is unclear what the exact situation is, but gunfire
can still be heard in different areas.

Al-Qusayr and surrounding towndestruction, looting, and random arrests
Assad forces continue their operations and attacks in Al-Qusayr, including
home raids, theft of property, and arrests of more than 15 confirmed people
since yesterday. The Assad forces also opened fire today at people coming
out of mosques, and the number of those injured is still unknown. The
attacks against the area are still ongoing.

Are these demonstrations or is this a dream?
Residents of Homs went out demonstrating in all areas of the city despite
all the brutality they have faced. The demonstrations were massive, calling
for Arabs to speak up and stop being silent, and to intervene. The residents
renewed the promise to continue. Residents of Al-Rastan went out after an
operation that induced the residents to go out, as did the residents of
Tadmur, and neighborhoods all over Homs.

Homs: Summary from Sunday, October 23, 2011

Today Homs gave 11 more martyrs:
1- Fathi Al-Hussami, under torture | Homs
2- A martyr from Shofan family | Homs | Bab Tadmur
3- Abdelwahed Albdeljabbar Arabi Al-Najjar | Homs | Bab Tadmur
4- Tarek Al-Ahdab | Homs | Al-Bayada
5- Jamal Abdullah Faddel | Homs | Al-Bayada
6- Adnan Mustapha Al-Dwayk, under torture | Homs | Al-Khaldiyeh
7- Mahmoud Al-Hamid Jassem, from torture wounds | Homs | Deir Balba
8- Taleb Al-Talawi | Homs | Karm Al-Shami
9- Abdel Rahman Al-Othman, a teacher | Homs | Deir Balba
10- Bilal Sroor | Homs | Al-Inshaat
11- Zainab Al-Sakka (female) | Homs | Deir Balba (from Hama and was returning to Hama from Faculty of Petro-Chemistry in Deir Balba, was killed by a bullet)

Drunk soldiershow can they be trusted with peoples lives?!
Around 11 am today, some residents and store owners from Al-Bayada neighborhood saw some soldiers who seemed drunk, coming out of the police station in Al-Bayada. The soldiers then started firing at people and cars in Deir Balba neighborhood. Later, tanks were seen in the neighborhood combing through the streets like Al-Nour and Al-Qahera streets. Rockets launched by the tanks burned many cars and at least two houses, in addition to injuring 6 people from Al-Bayada, among them one woman, in addition to 2 critical injuries. Another person was wounded in Al-Khaldiyeh. 3 young men were killed as a result of the attacks, and they are: Tarek Al-Ahdab as a result of the random gunfire in Al-Bayada, and Jamal Faddel who was trying to drag Tareks body from the street when he got shot, and a third martyr, who was shot from the checkpoint at the western entrance of Al-Khaldiyeh, his identity remains unknown. Cars exploded as a result of bombs falling on them and all over the neighborhood, and gunfire could be heard all day and into the evening in Deir Balba, Al-Khaldiyeh, and Al-Bayada in an attempt to impose a curfew on the area.  Here are some video from the neighborhoods today:

A man trying to grab a martyr in Al-Qahera streets ends up a martyr:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LpSXfpzvC-c
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NT9JmvH1QqE

Explosion of a power box in Al-Bayada because of bombs from tanks:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gAXDWES9bko

Hospitals, the wounded, and Shabihastudents are the reason
Assad forces and thugs, with the support of Assad army outside, raided Al-Hikma hospital in Al-Inshaat neighborhood and broke property inside the hospital along with medical equipment. They also looted the hospital and assaulted patients and injured people receiving treatment there. That took place after students went out demonstrating in the neighborhood, which bothered the security.

Student demonstration in Al-Inshaat:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=71R-QzKHuzw

Female students demonstrating in Al-Holeh today:

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aw3ECr1lDIY

Other Homs neighborhoods and surrounding towns
Power is still out in most neighborhoods and towns, along with communications and water. Movement around is very difficult, and the center of the city only saw activity for a few hours. Gunfire could be heard clearly in Talbiseh and in other neighborhoods in Homs. Funerals for yesterdays martyrs were very modest and small because of the heavy gunfire. It was also noticeable that many children were exhibiting signs of extreme fear and shock. In one example, one child has not spoken in over a month.

Some of the aftermath of bombing Al-Mrejeh neighborhood, where rockets seemed to have been used:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5FdcGjmluMA
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TxoT9EZc4gw

Demonstrations during explosions and air force bombing
Planes of the Assad military bombed Deir Balba today and there were reports of a lot of destruction, many homes burning, and smoke rising above the neighborhood. Many were wounded and there were martyrs, as residents were not able to get medical attention for them.

Video showing Deir Balba getting bombed by Assad air force
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HS1sufzFDpo

The bombing was not limited to Deir Balba, even though it got the most, as explosions were heard in Bab Al-Sbaa, Jib Al-Jandali, and Bab Draib. In Al-Waar, a black car driving around fired randomly at passersby in Rakan street, which resulted in wounding a young man and a little girl, who were attended to immediately. The car also threw a bomb of an unknown type, but it was a nail bomb near the place where a demonstration usually starts. Here is a video showing a girl who got hit by the nail bomb:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&v=vV22w-MTv-4

However, despite all this, the residents of Homs, who are clearly challenging oppression, went out from all neighborhoods and town to make their voices heard as they chanted for freedom. Here are some videos of evening demonstrations:

Homs: Summary from Wednesday, October 26, 2011

Al-Bayada under fireand its children are gifts for Bashar
On the day the Arab League delegation arrived to Syria, the residents of
Homs along with other Syrian cities decided to observe a general strike,
where people did not open their stores, students did not attend school, and
teachers and public employees did not show up to work. This enraged the
Assad forces and his cronies when they saw the residents of Homs respond to
the call for the general strike, so they opened fire at the closed stores
and bombed homes. This time, they aimed at families, and as a result, they
bombed the home of one family from which the grandmother, a little girl and
a brother, and the father and mother were struck. The little girl, Katrin
Khabour was killed. Here are some videos showing the family struck by a nail
bomb in Al-Bayada neighborhood, where the bomb was launched from Al-Zeer
checkpoint:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=il9PLhLx3kA

Child martyr Katrin Khabour, a gift to Bashar and the Arab League
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZRqSMgbl94s
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MmhJnccfxMY

A 4 year old boy was also killed, another gift from Bashar to the Arab
League
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0lOrMMAm3_s

Over than 10 people other than the above-mentioned family were also injured
in the same neighborhood, among then two children, one of them has been
killed most likely. Conditions in Al-Bayada and Baba Amro are very bad, and
gunfire still intermittently continues.

Here are some videos from Al-Bayada from today:

The neighborhoods of Homswho gives them a break?!
The rest of the neighborhoods and towns of Homs remain under fire. Baba
Amro, which everyday gets threatened, surrounded, and hit by all types of
weapons, witnessed severe panic today and smoke columns rose above the
neighborhood. Here are some videos from Baba Amro today:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FF47dgI5eF4
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LbpeFQlNDSc
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ajz-hAac4v0

As for Karm Al-Zeitoun that erupted against the Assad regime, was on the
receiving end of the Assad forces hatred today. Armored vehicles entered
the neighborhood and fired at its residents and looted its stores. Here are
some videos from the neighborhood today:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Pg2oX6mB7gY

Bab Al-Draib, Al-Nazeheen, Ashira, and Jib Al-Jandali neighborhoods did not
miss out on the action either. Assad forces opened fire on the residents of
these neighborhoods as well.

Shelling Jib Al-Jandali:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C48JNlpOZLw

StrikeDemonstrationsTake away whatever is left of the regimes sanity
Residents stayed at home, as no students, public employees, or business
owners worked today. Neighborhoods and towns of Homs responded to the strike
and stores remained closed today, so the Assad forces destroyed stores in
places like the historic Al-Kaisariyah and Al-Qusayr areas, where security
forces threatened residents to open their stores using mosque loudspeakers.

Homs: Summary from Thursday, October 27, 2011
Humanity is living in the previous century!

Rami Al-Dabbagthe martyr medic, is this how good guys get rewarded in my
country?
Jamal Faddel tried to help another guy in Al-Bayada, so snipers shot him.
And there are a lot more like Jamal. Here you have Rami Al-Dabbag who helps
the wounded in Al-Bayada, and as a result gets what good guys get in my
country. Their rewards is being killed and sniped, or at best being
arrested.

Martyr Rami Al-Dabbag
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UJaFewbjkoQ

Ramis funeral
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sLABrJPU46U

Another video of Rami Al-Dabbags funeral today
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EPG248PixaU

This morning, Assad forces arrested people who were trying to bring bread
into Al-Bayada neighborhood, which was bombed for the last few days. As
people try to help the residents, they get their rewards of being arrested.

Students demonstratethe solution is to kill them so they will not
demonstrate
This morning and as soon as some students went to their schools and
universities, some security checkpoints stated firing at people and
students. Assad security forces then spread around the city center among the
troublemakers and started harassing passersby, men and women. Today, Assad
soldiers, who were supposed to get back the Golan Heights for Syria, have
become bandits, criminals, and children killers. In other neighborhoods,
Assad forces terrorized residents by opening fire randomly, then laughing.
Gunfire could be heard in the heart of Homs, the sounds of the same bullets,
which are directed at the heart of each person in Homs.
In the evening, armored vehicles opened fire in Deir Balba, Joret Al-Shayah,
Al-Khaldiyeh, and Baba Amro.

Signs of bombing in Karm Al-Zeitoun

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ECDmT-7BPcs

Bombing of Al-Qusayr today
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E8NY9YonjvI

http://www.youtube.com/watch?hl=ar&amp;v=DUtn71Zwlkg

Shabiha thugs are also car thieves  Al-Khaldiyeh
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ofQHJp8-0pQ

Demonstrations for more than 250 dayswhere are those who can understand?
Evening demonstrations go out after demonstrations that went out earlier in
the day. This goes on everyday, with persistence. There is something new
everyday, and the people want international protection, no-fly zone, and
execution of the president on top of their lists. At the same time, Arab
leaders give Assad more time to kill the children and the elderly.  Here are
some sample videos of demonstrations from today:

Homs: Summary of Events from No Fly Zone Friday, October 28, 2011

23 Homs confirmed martyrs from Friday

Taher Al-Jamrak, 80 | Homs | Al-Qusayr
Ahmad Kujek, 31 | Homs | Baba Amro

Wednesday | Homs

Nader Abdelmueen Al-Sajj | Homs | Karm Al-Zeitoun

First, we should remind ourselves that our martyrs are not just numbers or
a publicity tool, they are the greatest on the face of the Earth,
sacrificing selflessly their blood so we can reach a noble life of freedom.
Our sons wounds, the detention of our brothers, the harm our young men
see, and the torture our freedom heroes receive is not just for publicity,
it is a wound in the conscience of our nation, and an incentive for us to
continue, defend, support, and help. So please, honor the blood of the
martyrs, and know that victory is ours. So let us keep our promise to
staying the course, patience, victory, and forgiveness.

Like every night, the sounds of gunfire and explosions were heard in most
neighborhoods. Their source was the checkpoints that are spread in all
areas.

The Shabiha thugs attacked at dawn Al-Shammas, a poor resilient
neighborhood, to terrorize the residents with heavy presence of the Assad
forces.

Shabiha attacking Al-Shammas neighborhood
http://youtu.be/XaSXXs9uJf8
http://youtu.be/ztHrlrL4PpY

Reports came in from Karm Al-Zeitoun and Al-Nazeheen about the passing of
martyr Nader Abdelmoeen Al-Saj after being shot by security forces
yesterday.

Snipers spread on top of the Homs Citadel, which overlooks Bab Al-Sbaa
neighborhood, targeted and killed martyr Mahmoud Atiyah this morning before
the Friday prayer.

Homs with all its neighborhoods and surrounding towns and villages
revolted, even those under siege. Demonstrations went out in each of: Bab
Al-Draib, Al-Warsha, Bab Houd, Saliba Al-Asyati, Jib Al-Jandali,
Al-Hamidiyeh, Al-Shammas, Al-Qusoor, Deir Balba, Al-Bayada, Al-Khaldiyeh,
Masaken Al-Moalimeen, Joret Al-Shayah, Al-Karabees, Al-Inshaat, Baba Amro,
Joret Al-Arayes, Jobar, Al-Sultaniyeh, Kafar Aya, Karm Al-Zeitoun,
Al-Bazeheen, Al-Midan, Karm Al-Shami, Ashira, Al-Ghouta, Al-Hamra, Bab
Al-Sbaa, Ter Maaleh, Al-Ghanto, Al-Qusayr, Talbiseh, Al-Rastan, Ezz
El-Deen, Al-Sikhneh, Al-Bayoda Al-Sharqiyeh, Tadmur, Al-Qayatain, and
Al-Holeh.

The Assad forces and thugs fired at demonstrators in most neighborhoods,
especially in Al-Ghouta, Bab Al-Draib, Baba Amro, Al-Inshaat, Al-Khaldiyeh
(where nail bombs were used against demonstrators), Al-Bayada, Bab Al-Sbaa,
Deir Balba, Al-Nazeheen, Karm Al-Zeitoun, Al-Qusayr, Talbiseh, and
Al-Rastan. Tens were injured, including women and children, some with
serious injuries. A large number of martyrs also fell, among them from
Al-Qusayr, 80 year old Taher Jamrak, and Riad Al-Rez and Waleed Al-Nasser
from Al-Rastan. There were also from Baba Amro, Dr. Ali Al-Hazouri, Ahmad
Kajak, Abdelrahman Al-Soufi, Mahmoud Janseez, Muhammad Naseef, Ali
Al-Rahmouni, Muhammad Ali Azmili, and two women martyrs, Om Badawi, Haifa
Al-Kurdi. Other martyrs were Asaad Muhammad Diab (Ashira), Jassem Al-Khalif
Al-Khaldi and Ziad Al-Deen Khatib (Dier Balba), Abdelmalek Al-Zain and
Abdelbari Al-Zain (Al-Khaldiyeh), and Muna Fatrawi (Al-Bayada), Taher
Al-Bunni (Bab Al-Sbaa), and Bassam Mahmoud Hamdi (Karm Al-Zeitoun and
Al-Nazeheen).

Even when the demonstrations dispersed, armored vehicles, tanks, and
checkpoints continued to launch rockets and fire with machines guns towards
the neighborhoods, especially Al-Bayada, where homes were destroyed, fire
erupted, and fire trucks and ambulances were not allowed to enter the
neighborhood. Things were also tough in Al-Khaldiyeh, where a lot of nail
bombs were launched from armored vehicles. In Deir Balba, heavy artillery
was used to demolish the neighborhood. Things were also tough in Karm
Al-Zeitoun, Al-Nazeheen, Jib Al-Jandali, Baba Amro (where there were many
injured who were impossible to attend to because of the heavy gunfire and
siege of the neighborhood), Bab Al-Sbaa, Al-Waar (where there were violent
clashes in the military academy), Bab Al-Draib (where Kaab Al-Ahbar mosque
was targeted), Al-Inshaat, and Joret Al-Shayah. The same was true for the
towns of Talbiseh, Al-Qusayr, and Al-Rastan.

Demonstrations went out even though the Assad forces surrounded many
mosques, threatened to arrest the Imams, and fired during and after prayer,
as happened in Al-Qusayr and many mosques in Homs like Bilal Al-Habashi
mosque on the Damascus road, Omar Bin Al-Khatab mosque, and many others.

News arrived about intense shelling of Al-Bayada with heavy artillery and
tanks amid confirmed news of defection of many soldiers, who burned the
military vehicles they had before they fled seeking shelter with the
residents.

Many mourners of martyr Taher Jamrak in Al-Qusayr were threatened and
targeted by Lt. Col. Ammar Al-Jarf the head of the military security branch
in the city. He threatened that anyone who goes out in the martyrs funeral
would be buried next to him. He also forced the martyrs family to sign a
declaration that gangs were the ones that killed him. At least two people
were injured during the funeral.

Al-Qusayr | Martyr Taher Jamraks funeral
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L61gH1n-vps

There was also news about the passing of martyr Abdel Muneem Abbas
Al-Riadi, whos more than 80 years old, as a result of wounds sustained
after being shot by Shabiha thugs on Wednesday morning, the day of the
general strike.

Gunfire and explosions did not stop even after supper time, and remained
intermittent in Al-Waar, Al-Inshaat, Baba Amro, Al-Bayada, Al-Khaldiyeh,
Deir Balba, Bab Al-Sbaa, Bab Al-Draib, Al-Khard, and Al-Midan.  Evening
demonstrations also went out in the towns of Al-Holeh, Tadmur, Al-Qusayr,
Tal Kalakh, and the neighborhoods of Al-Inshaat, Joret Al-Shayah,
Al-Karabees, Jin Al-Jandali, Karm Al-Shami, Al-Khaldiyeh, Al-Qusoor, Bab
Houd, Al-Hamra, Bab Al-Draib, Karm Al-Zeitoun, Al-Nazeheen, Al-Bayada, Deir
Balba, Al-Shammas, and Al-Ghouta.

Assad thugs and militias opened fire on demonstrators to disperse them in
Jib Al-Jandali, Bab Houd, and Al-Inshaat (where reportedly nail bombs and
bullets were fired from a Shabiha car towards worshipers leaving Al-Fardous
mosque, and injuries were reported). An armored vehicle entered Bab Al-Sbaa
and fired hysterically. In addition, the air force intelligence checkpoint
in Tal Kalakh opened fire at homes, cars, and demonstrators returning, but
no injuries were reported.

Firing continued from the checkpoints, armored vehicles, and tanks
stationed at the checkpoints towards the neighborhoods. Heavy artillery
demolished Baba Amro and Bab Al-Sbaa, where columns of fire and smoke were
seen rising from some places in the neighborhood, and all residents could
do was to chant for God. Gunfire resumed inside the military academy in
Al-Waar, without getting any news from there, except ambulances carrying
injured people. Some military trucks and tanks were also seen wandering
some neighborhoods or on main roads like Nizar Qabbani street towards
Al-Ghouta and Tripoli road towards Al-Inshaat and Baba Amro. A huge
explosion was heard in Al-Inshaat after a period of gunfire, and residents
chanting Gods name in response. Residents of Al-Waar also heard heavy
gunfire from the police station and the neighborhoods checkpoints.

In Talbiseh, checkpoints and tanks that support them fired rockets and
machine guns towards Al-Masjer Al-Janoubi neighborhood. No injuries were
reported.

The sounds of explosions and smoke clouds continued to rise up in Bab
Al-Sbaa and Al-Khudr neighborhoods. There was confirmed news of the
defection of a number of officers and tens of soldiers, and targeting the
Citadel and Al-Farabi checkpoints, and the area around the Citadel, then
fleeing to seek shelter with the residents. As a result, the neighborhood
was targeted and power was cut from it. Same thing in Baba Amro, where a
lot of explosions were heard amid a power outage in the entire neighborhood
and intense gunfire. Same was the situation in Al-Bayada where gunfire did
not stop, and the neighborhood did not stop giving its sons between martyr
and injured.

Bab Al-Sbaa | Intense gunfire and explosions all around
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cUn0Dy7ceg0

weapons in Al-Waar, Al-Shammas, around the university residence halls, Karm
Al-Shami, Damascus road, and other areas.

Homs: Summary of Events to this moment from Saturday, October 29, 2011

Another day of savagery, destruction, and killing by the Assad forces
Homs started its day with sounds of bombing that was louder and more
intense than usual, aimed at Baba Amro. More than 20 explosions were heard
and they shook the neighborhood. Smoke clouds could be seen clearly from
nearby neighborhoods rising from Baba Amro. Heavy artillery and tank bombs
were used to target the neighborhood violently and snipers were used to
paralyze movement in the streets. Explosions and machine guns continue to
be heard, even in most Homs neighborhoods. Assad security also bombed
Al-Hamza mosque.

Bombing Al-Hamze mosque in Baba Amro today
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OHrtr5ZmSEg

Bombing Baba Amro with heavy artillery and machine guns
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JZ7jUvm6MAk
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sIeusScgeEI

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KWE3KHQpfYY

Targeting a photographer while he was taking pictures
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A-SCNJZJnsU

Some of the types of ammunition used in the bombing
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KWE3KHQpfYY

One of the homes that was bombed
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jPG398OLZlo

Military planes were used in these inhumane bombing operations
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4Xk1BsvJJhM

A demonstration went out in Baba Amro despite the destruction and the power
outage
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iRpMmVwM9gM

The bombing reached other neighborhoods near Baba Amro, where two bombs
fell in the area between Al-Qubaa mosque and Al-Hikma hospital, but luckily
without injuring anyone. Fires were seen in the Baath University near the
Faculty of medicine, which is close to the area being bombed. In continued
attempts to mislead media by the Assad regime, two medical student
residence halls that overlook Baba Amro, were emptied so none of them could
capture what the regime was doing to the innocent people in the
neighborhood.

In Deir Balba, a young man, Khaled Hasan Al-Yaseen was stopped at the
checkpoint by the Deir Balba-Al-Bayada traffic sign, and after he passed
through and was 50 meters away, they shot him from the back. The bullet
went through the car, his body, and the front windshield, and he died.
There were also two explosions that shoot Al-Janoubi area of Deir Balba,
and reportedly, a young man was injured in the shoulder and is in critical
condition.

A young man, Mahmoud Al-Nimr was shot and killed by a sniper at Al-Atrash
circle
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KPRj3U-mns0

In Jib Al-Jandali, martyr Mulham Al-Shlar, 25 years old, died after he was
shot by an armored vehicle stationed in the neighborhood. The security
checkpoint in the neighborhood arrested 6 young men and took them to an
unknown location, and to this time there is no information about them.

In Al-Bayada, 2 armored vehicles passed in Al-Qahera street and started
firing heavily, which greatly terrorized residents, who fled home to escape
the gunfire, leaving their stores open. Gunfire was shot intermittently
from Al-Zer checkpoint towards homes and an unannounced curfew was imposed.
Movement completely stopped in Al-Qahera street. Abo Al-Nour, 60 years old,
who owns a vegetable carriage, was arrested in Al-Bayada after he was
injured by gunfire and his carriage was destroyed, which is his main source
of income.

Al-Khadr neighborhood was also completely surrounded and Assad forces fired
randomly to terrorize the residents. Assad thugs then spread around to
carry out inspections and further terrorize the residents. Seeing as there
was heavy gunfire, there was no noon prayer in Othman mosque.

Since the morning, Assad forces started raiding some homes in Al-Karama
area in Bab Al-Sbaa, and surrounding area looking for soldiers who defected
last night. The sniper who is located on top of the Citadel targeted young
man, Mahmoud Atyah with two bullets, one in the head and the other in the
stomach. A funeral was held for the martyr after the evening prayer.

The systemic terrorizing practiced by the Assad forces continued, and a new
checkpoint was placed at the Baath branch building in Al-Inshaat to
increase the siege on the residents and to be able to carry out more
terrorizing operations.

In Al-Khaldiyeh, a funeral was held for the two martyr brothers, Abdelbari
and Abdelmalek Al-Zain, who were killed yesterday by Assad forces bullets
during a peaceful demonstration calling for freedom. Here is a video clip
of the brothers funeral:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JQliA9NoMKs

In Talbiseh, a 40 year old lady, Fatima Abdo Al-Deekh was killed by a
bullet to the head from snipers at one of the checkpoints in the area.
Fatima took care of orphans and she was going with two of her grandchildren
to the barber shop, when the sniper at the athletic club checkpoint
targeted her.  Here are video clips of martyr Fatima:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8EpGkltURU0
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eZztR-4dadk

As if that were not enough for the checkpoint, Assad forces there fired two
bullets at a pedestrian, one hitting him in the hand, and the other hit him
in the back and came out of his stomach. Luckily he survived somehow and he
is in a stable condition. Residents should be warned about this checkpoint
that fires randomly, and we warn people from going near an remnants from
the Assad forces, as a 12 year old child yesterday in Talbiseh came near an
exploded bomb and when he touched it, it exploded and he lost three fingers
on his left hand and bad disfigurement to his face, while his eyes are
still shut to this moment.

Since early morning, intermittent gunfire from machine guns could be heard
in Al-Qusayr as a reminder to the residents of the presence of the Assad
forces.

There was an explosion in Tadmur from the direction of the airport, and its
nature is still unknown. Military aircraft was also observed in the area.

A demonstration went out in Joret Al-Shayah after the evening prayer in
solidarity with Baba Amro, and in it, the demonstartors called for imposing
a no-fly zone to deter the Assad forces and its cronies.

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OXQ3Vjac28c
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4NTGt5YKE_U
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ls5rwhW7mfA
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wUzS8AfzSXI
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PBmyhygBgio

A store was set on fire in Karm Al-Zeitoun by Assad thugs because of the
strike
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RuKf4huQ88g

So far today, there are 9 confirmed martyrs
Nasser Al-Hamwi | Homs | Baba Amro
Mahmoud Jnaid | Homs | Baba Amro
Khaled Hasan Al-Yaseen | Homs | Deir Balba
Muhammad Abdel Azziz Al-Taleb | Homs | Deir Balba
Fatima Al-Deekh, 45 | Homs | Talbiseh
Muhammad Muslmani, 90 | Homs | Baba Amro
Muhammad Mulham Shnar | Homs | Jib Al-Jandali
Nour El-Deen Al-Attar | Homs | Jib Al-Jandali
Mahmoud Al-Nimr | Homs | Deir Balba

SRGC | Hama | 28/10/2011 | Summary:
Summary of events in Hama on 28 Oct 20111; Friday of demanding a No-Fly-Zone
Martyrs:
The whole city rose up in a harsh day on this Friday, despite the hardship
the peoples will was not deterred and the challenge inspired them to be
even more determined to demand their freedom and to topple the regime, Hama
is still sacrificing martyrs, following are the names we have-till now- of
martyrs who fell on this Friday:
1. Muhammad Darwish Al-Izz
2. Rasmiya Farhan; the mother of the above martyr, in Janoub Al-Malaab
neighborhood
3. Hasan Saleh Bashouri, Al-Jarajmeh neighborhood
4. Ahmed Al-Martini
5. Yahya Al-martini; brother of the above martyr Ahmed Al-Martini
6. Muhammad Al-Qahit
7. Khalid Al-Ali
8. Muhammad Akir, a child
9. Khalid Abdul-Hadi
10. Bassam Klib
11. Alaa Al-Tabl
12. A young man from Al-Kabir family

The fascist regime thinks that by killing the defenseless and the innocent,
the people will be intimidated and would stop demanding their freedom, what
the dim regime does not understand is that those who taste injustice and
death acquire a will that can bend steel and that-for them- fear of death
becomes a faint illusion.

Demonstrations:
Demonstration issued from the following mosques:
Al-Manakh, Abdul-Rahman Bin Awf, Al-Shuhada, Uthman Bin Affan, Al-Hamza,
Al-Tawhid, Al-Falah, Al-Noor, Muath Bin Jabal, Al-Mumenin, Al-Sarjawi,
Al-nasan, Al-Masri.

Clashes, defection, and regime forces crimes:
-An explosion in Al-Qusour neighborhood left more than a dozen Shabiha
(regime-sponsored gangs) dead.
-Raids and random arrests in Al-Sabouniya neighborhood.
-The boxing champion and soldier Ahmed Wattar and 2 of his neighbors were
arrested in Al-Sabouniya neighborhood.
- The worshipers inside the mosque of Abdul-Rahman Bin Awf were besieged, 4
were martyred and many were wounded while inside the mosque.
- Clashes between members of the Free Syrian Army who were protecting the
demonstration and Security forces around the mosque of Al-Sarjawi
- The mosque of Salah Al-Din in the neighborhood of Jaonub Al-Malab was
surrounded before Fridays prayers [at noon]. Security forces launched
sound-bombs during the Fridays sermon.
-Heavy gunfire and barbaric attacks by security forces and Shabiha
(regime-sponsored gangs) in all of the following neighborhoods and streets;
Al-Hadir, Al-Hamidiya, Al-Jub, 40 Street, Al-Qusour, Thee Qar Street,
Janoub Al-Malaab, Al-Alamayn Street, Al-Shajara market, and Al-Husseiniyat.
-For the 1st time defection by large groups take place intensively in Hama.
- Clashes between members of the Free Syrian Army and regime forces in all
of the neighborhoods in Hama.
- A large group of elements stationed in Janoub Al-Malaab-close by
Al-Forousiya roundabout, defected from the army and joined the Free Syrian
Army after destroying an armored vehicle, a bus and a car and killing more
than 30 of Shabiha (regime-sponsored gangs).
- Reports of the defection of more than 20 privates and officers from
security forces.
- A large number of armored vehicles and tanks are surrounding the mosque
of Al-Sarjawi. Troop carriers are present in Al-Jarajmeh neighborhood.
-Security forces and Shabiha (regime-sponsored gangs) surrounded the
worshipers inside Al-Sarjawi mosque, Sheikh Mustafa [a religious figure]
called authorities to allow the worshipers to leave, in the meantime
reigmes snipers stationed on the roofs of high buildings, were shooting at
anything that moves in the streets.
-More than 15 were martyred or wounded in Al-Jarajmeh neighborhood.

properties.description:
Summary of events in Hama, on 30 Oct 2011



Since the early hours, there was intensive gunfire in Kafr Zita [Rural
Hama]. Then after noon prayers 1,000s of Kafr Nabouda [another town in
Hamas rural] took part in the funeral procession of Mahmoud Qamiro, who
was killed by the regimes gangs.

Unprecedented heavy presence of security forces in the city of Hama;
security forces set up more checkpoints-barricades and all cars were
subjected to extensive inspections.



Students demonstrations and regime forces response:

A quick students demonstration was held in Al-Karama neighborhood, the
demonstration called for the execution of the president and chanted in
solidarity with wounded Homs. In Al-Qusour neighborhood, after school,
students from Samir Sawwaf middle school held a demonstration, and security
forces arrested one of the children-students. Demonstrations also issued
from the schools of Khalid Samak and Haitham Asaya, security forces faced
these demonstrations with teargas causing asphyxia cases between the
children-students.

Since the early hours, security forces conducted a savage campaign on the
schools in the neighborhood of Gharb Al-Mashtal, terrorizing school
children, insulting, harassing and bullying them. Security forces also used
profanities and insults against all of the neighborhoods residents because
of the pro-revolution phrases written on the walls, residents were forced
to cover the writings, note that all the phrases were signed by the Spray
man [Young men wearing masks and writing on the walls pro-revolution
phrases, they are called Spray men; it is a phenomenon in the revolution
taking place all over Syria, these young men could face torture and death
if they are caught by the regime].

In Al-Baiad neighborhood, students demonstrations issued from the schools
of Ibn Khaldoun and Tashrin. Some students from the school of Uthman
Al-Hourani in the neighborhood of Aleppo-road distributed leaflet calling
for civil disobedience for a week starting same day, 30 Oct.

Large demonstrations took place in rural Hama in the towns of Taibat
Al-Imam, Morak, Khattab, and Halfaya. In Suran, students of Rakan Salem
high school held a set-in under the banner of Set-ins till the regime
falls, during the set-in, security agents raided the students and arrested
3 of them, angering the rest of the students who then went immediately in a
tour for all of the schools and tore down the pictures of the tyrant
[meaning Bashar Al-Assad] from principles offices. The rebel heroes of
Suran sent the following message to security forces: If the detained
students are not released within the hour, we will respond in action and
not in words. Security forces were forced, under pressure, to release the
students.



Regime forces violence and peoples position:

The army and Shabiha (regime-sponsored gangs) stormed the countryside of
Hama; a huge military campaign of more than 30 vehicles full of security
and Shabiha elements stormed the villages of Khunaizir [Khnezir] and
Al-Jelma [Jalama].

And in Al-Sqilbiya, security, Shabiha (regime-sponsored gangs), and army
forces with around 30 vehicles stormed the city of Al-Sqilbiya along with a
raid campaign.

Hayalin village was stormed by the army, security forces, and Shabiha
(regime-sponsored gangs) who entered the village firing at passers-by,
injuring a truck driver who was transporting government-sponsored feed to
Sahl Al-Ghab.

In Khattab town, the detainee Shadi Al-Hasan, was delivered dead to his
family, when he was arrested, 3 days earlier, he was in good health.

A general strike took place everywhere in Kernaz town in mourning of
martyrs.

2:00 PM: 4 armored vehicles at Al-Dhaheriya checkpoint-barricade; the
vehicles faced the 4 directions and were hid by sand barricades.

6:30 PM: Large numbers of Shabiha arrived on green buses [Shabiha buses] at
Al-Assad medical plaza.

During the evening, many demonstrations were held in the neighborhoods of
Al-Jarajmeh, Al-Sharqiya, Al-Hamidiya, Al-Qusour, and Aleppo-road.

Despite the threats by regime forces, a large demonstration was held in
Kafr Zita, condemning, in resentment, the Arab League, and chanting in
solidarity with Homs; saying that We are with you till death.
Demonstrations were also held in Taibat Al-Imam, Morak, and Al-Twina.

9:30: A raid campaign along with a number of home break-ins at the
backstreet of Al-Thalathin (30) Street, with the presence of an armored
vehicle, and elements of security and Shabiha (regime-sponsored gangs).

9:45 PM: Heavy gunfire in Al-Karama neighborhood. 2 army tanks were
observed at Al-Dhaheriya Bridge, with a number of troop carriers and
armored vehicles. Security forces were deployed close by Al-Noor mosque in
Al-Alelayat neighboehood- near Al-Sabouniya neighborhood, the sound of one
bullet was heard.

Syria crisis
Avaaz diplomatic briefing / analysis
Thursday November 3, 2011

Current situation in Homs
The Syrian army, security forces and Shabiha death squads are still in the
city of Homs. At 3am this morning, tanks started shelling the northeast
area of Baba Amr neighbourhood. Enshaat district in Homs was raided by
security forces supported by death squads, who targeted houses searching
for activists.
Military reinforcements from Hama arrived to Homs in the early hours of
this morning.
Two nights ago, an armed resistance group in Homs kidnapped and killed 9
Alawites, severely stoking sectarian tensions and provoking retaliatory
attacks on Sunni in a tissue factory in Hawla. Sources from Alawite
neighbourhoods claimed that the attack on the tissue factory and killing of
11 Sunni workers was a spontaneous reaction from people in the Alawite
community, and that the army was not involved in the incident.

Avaaz has been working hard to calm the rising sectarian tensions in
Homs. Wissam
Tarif, Arabic campaigner at Avaaz, said: Since the early hours of this
morning we have been engaging activists in talks with community leaders
from both sides. It is crucial to note that retaliatory attacks are
provoked by the regime in Homs. Unlike in other parts of the country where
death squads are brought in from other regions, death squads operating in
Homs are from neighbouring towns. Those looking to exact revenge on the
Alawite death squads are targeting anyone in their own Alawite community as
a result. The regime strategy is to specifically and very deliberately
incite division between Alawites and Sunnis in Homs. Community leaders from
both sides understand what is happening. The attacks are sowing the seeds
of very personal and long-term violence, as the vendetta will lead to
specific families being targeted. The situation so far is containable and
opposition figures are talking with Sunni clerics to calm people down.
Alawite artists and intellectuals are dealing with the Alawite groups
intent on violence.

Weapons trade
The number of Syrians buying weapons in Lebanon has increased significantly
during the last three weeks. Lebanese businesses selling hunting weapons
are flourishing - especially in the Bekaa Valley. Nevertheless smuggling
operations in general into Syria from Bekaa have not been effective and the
smuggling of weapons has been seriously hampered by the regime, which is
determined to stop weapons from getting into the Damascus suburbs.
Ambushes by armed gangs were reported in Zabadani and Madaya last month,
nevertheless we are seeing less and less of it now as the regime has
tightened up security significantly along that stretch of the border.
Still, the smuggling of cigarettes and other goods is operating without
hindrance. Smuggling networks have been penetrated by regime security
forces and is a main source of income for many of them. Therefore they
decide what gets through and what doesnt.
On the northern Lebanese border, Syrian activists have developed close ties
to arms traders in Lebanon. Their operation is still on a small scale and
primarily financed by Syrians in the diaspora, although we know that some
people in Homs have even sold the furniture from their homes to buy weapons
and smuggle them into Homs.

Having met with Lebanese politicians, activists, smugglers and Homs
residents who are active on the military front, we have come to the
conclusion that no Lebanese political party is involved in smuggling
weapons into Syria. Due to the relatively small volume of trade, it is
clear that no country is involved in financing the weapons smuggling to
Syria.

A prominent Lebanese politician known for being opposed to the Assad
regime, said: Lebanon cannot afford to destabilize the Syrian regime.
Smuggling is taking place under the regimes nose. They see it and they
allow it. It takes them less than two hours to secure their border and stop
any form of weapon smuggling inside their border. The weapons trade is
manipulated by the Syrian regime and using usual networks to list what is
allowed and what is not allowed to be sold to Syrian activists. The
operation is fully exposed to Syrian security forces.
The implication of these remarks is that the Syrian regime is actively
trying to foment violence, knowing that it needs to allow a certain amount
of armed resistance to the continued crackdown in order to verbally justify
its heavy-handed repression of the protesters.

Arab League initiative
It had been expected that the regime would accept the initiative, and throw
the ball in the Syrian National Councils court by proposing dialogue. The
SNC is in a difficult position. Protesters demands are clear - they are
anti-dialogue and against any political process not focused on regime
change.
Borhan Ghalioun, the president of the Syrian National Council released a
statement today, regarding the Arab League deal with the Assad regime. He
said that the acceptance of the Arab League initiative by the regime does
not mean that the regime will respect the clauses of this agreement.
He asked for assurances, in summary:
1.  The immediate implementation of all the provisions of the initiative
before the start of any negotiations in order to test the intentions of the
regime. Specifically, the SNC expects the army to withdraw from cities and
to stop the killing of civilians.
2.   The appointment of human rights committees and organizations to
document the abuses faced by detainees as well as to hold the perpetrators
accountable.
3.  The involvement of the United Nations in order to ensure implementation
and compliance.
4. A deadline for the regime to fully implement the initiative.

Dima Moussa, a member of the Syrian National Council, told Avaaz today: The
regime has been violating the Arab League Initiative from the moment it
agreed to it. The military offensive against Homs today, especially in Baba
Amr, since agreeing two days ago to immediately stop military operations
against the civilians, was a clear violation. We encourage everyone to
monitor what the regime is doing, by sending in human rights observers or
the media, which by the regime's own agreement, should be allowed into
Syria to travel around to freely and observe and report the conditions
inside.

Homs: Summary from Tuesday, October 25, 2011

A demonstration went out before noon in Al-Holeh, with the news of the
arrival of reinforcements that got stationed in the center of the town.

In the morning, Shabiha thugs kidnapped the Muezzin of Al-Wafai mosque in
Al-Inshaat neighborhood after the morning prayer and took him to Al-Thahab
neighborhood, which is pro-regime. Later, people found his body on the road
to Tadmur, and a quiet funeral was held for him without a demonstration
because the Assad security and Shabiha thugs threatened his family.

Heavy gunfire was fired from machine guns and rockets were launched from
tanks from the checkpoints spread all along Al-Qahera street in Al-Bayada
neighborhood, and they were aimed at residential homes and at stores. Some
of the snipers located inside and on top of the postal services building
aimed at pedestrians. As a result of all of this, some stores burned and
many homes got damages, in addition to many injuries to people. The firing
and rockets were also fired in each of Al-Khaldiyeh, Al-Qusoor, and Deir
Balba neighborhoods. Reportedly, two young men from Al-Khaldiyeh were
arrested.

The Assad security and Shabiha thugs raid Al-Khaldiyeh neighborhood
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z1T7JFdV9R8

Firing at cars and homes in Al-Khaldiyeh
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=waxaB-lOJ60
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8Oc_9nsIdwQ

Most stores closed when a group of security members located at the police
headquarters near the Old Clock started firing to intimidate people.

A few more checkpoints were established inside the city to further divide
the city and terrorize the residents. For example, new checkpoints were
added in Al-Karabees and Al-Qusoor.

The Shabiha militias, with the support of the Assad regime, continued
kidnapping and killing people. 3 cars, one of them a taxi, kidnapped a woman
in full hijab (or Niqab) in Al-Waar neighborhood near Al-Kawakibi caf and
going towards the refinery circle (most likely towards Al-Mazraa, which is
mostly Shia Muslims).

In the afternoon, a massive demonstration went out in Al-Bayada with
participation from women. As a result, checkpoints and security members
fired at the demonstration, resulting in some wounded.

News came from Al-Qusayr about the arrest of Abdelmamoon Awda from his home,
and he is the brother of martyr Mahmoud Awda. Mahmoud Al-Zuhoori, 65 years
old, was also arrested at one of the checkpoints. Others who were reportedly
arrested: Muhammad Muheb El-Deen, Muhammad Al-Shalabi, Ammar Rad, and Isam
Akram Idrees (16 years old).

In Al-Bayoda village, just east of Al-Qusayr, a funeral was held for martyr
Abdelraheem Moussa Bakar, who was killed by Assad forces bullets in Karm
Al-Zeitoun neighborhood of Homs while he was there.
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5gs_K9U2sYY

Reports arrived from Talbiseh about arresting 4 people from one family from
their home, in Al-Janoubi neighborhood this morning and they are: Kamal,
Najib, Ammer, and Ammar Al-Nasan.

The city of Homs witnessed more violent bombing and firing operations from
checkpoints and armored vehicles, even in side streets. The minarets of Saad
Bin Abi Wakkas and Oman Bin Al-Khattab mosques were targeted. There were
many injuries and wounded people, including children and women, one child
who is 11 years old is in critical condition after being shot in the neck.
The operation continued until the early evening. Additionally, Fatima Khaled
Al-Daheek, 42 years old, a mother of 5 was also killed. It should be noted
that her bother is martyr Muhammad Khaled Al-Daheek and her husband has been
arrested and detained for over 3 months now.

Talbiseh | A child is shot in his chest by a sniper and is in critical
condition
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ar93snRVs58

Talbiseh | Heavy gunfire and armored vehicles combing the streets
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HYvYGtI5uxk
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tWGuw7XglZA

Talbiseh | Signs of the shelling and destruction in one home
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KWPdII2gZ5A
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R-bQKRH0cvM
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X66es9N_-tQ

Before sunset, two armored vehicles fired heavily in the streets of Jib
Al-Jandali, which resulted in a lot of damage. Checkpoints and armored
vehicles in Al-Bayada resumed firing and launching bombs towards residential
homes, with the sounds of explosions being heard all around. As for Deir
Balba, which had been viciously attacked the last few days, Assad forces
used heavy artillery, machine guns, and bombs to bomb the neighborhood,
which resulted in many wounded. It should be noted that there were reports
of Shabiha thugs kidnapping a young man, Mahdi Al-Sharif, 33 years old, and
taking him to Al-Abbasiyeh neighborhood, then an unknown location.

Despite all the shelling and misery around the city, demonstrations still
went out in the evening in different neighborhoods and towns around Homs,
calling for a general strike tomorrow, which is being called for all over
Syria. Some examples are demonstrations in Al-Qusoor, Al-Waar, Baba Amro,
Joret Al-Arayes, Al-Inshaat, Al-Ghouta, Al-Hamra, Bab Al-Sbaa, Al-Karabees,
Joret Al-Shayah, Al-Khaldiyeh, Al-Bayada, Bab Houd, Karm Al-Shami, Al-Midan,
Karm Al-Zeitoun, Al-Nazeheen, Jib Al-Jandali, Al-Shammas, Ashira, Al-Holeh
and surrounding towns, Al-Qusayr, and Tadmur. Shabiha thugs attacked
demonstrators in Al-Qusayr near the clinic, and several injuries were
reported. In Al-Ghouta, armored vehicles dispersed the demonstration, and
Assad forces used gunfire and bombs in Al-Nazeheen, Deir Balba, and Bab
Al-Sbaa, with injuries reported there too.

properties.incident translation: Summary of events in the city of Hama on Tuesday, 25 Oct 2011
properties.description:
Summary of events in the city of Hama on Tuesday, 25 Oct 2011
As every day, the army aircraft penetrate the sound barrier in the skies of
Hama, and flew low over Mehrada.
Students demonstrations were held in Hama city, including a demonstration
in Al-Taawoniya neighborhood; the demonstration issued from the schools of
Ibn Khaldoun, Mukhtar Al-Asheq, Al-Yarmouk, and Uqba Bin Nafea. Another
demonstration was held in the neighborhood of Gharb Al-Mashtal and it issued
from the school of Bassam Hamsho.
In the province of Hama, students demonstrations were held in Kafr Zita,
demonstrators cursed the soul of Hafez [Hafez Al-Assad is the late
president, a war criminal, he destroyed Hama in the 80s, and the father of
the current president], and other demonstrations were held in Kafr Nabouda,
Khattab, and Al-Tarimseh.
In the town of Qastoun in Sahl Al-Ghab area, the army forces fired randomly
at the agricultural lands surrounding the barricades-checkpoints, horrifying
the residence and causing some of them to leave their homes and flee to
other areas with no army presence.
The Syrian television tried to trick people for interviews in Al-Asi square
[in Hama city] by claiming they are from the Russia Today TV station, and
by adding the Russian channels logo to their microphones. An eyewitness
identified the camera man as an employee of the Syrian TV channel.
An unidentified dead body was found in Sahl Al-Ghab, the victim was
apparently burned and killed.
Around 4 pm, 7 security and Shabiha [regime-sponsored gangs] cars arrived at
Al-Hadir area [in Hama city] and arrested a man who is not older than 35
years old and works in the fishing business.
Around 6 pm, there was a campaign of raids at the old Aleppo-road area [in
Hama city] in the street of Al-Shallal restaurant.
After nighttime prayers, a large demonstration issued from Al-Shuhada
[martyrs] mosque in the neighborhood of Al-Sabouniya. The chants were: God
is greater [than the oppressor], calling for freedom and the fall of the
president, and in solidarity with Homs, Daraa, and other cities under attack
by Al-Assad army [the regimes army].
Demonstrations were also held in the neighborhoods of Al-Hamidiya and
Al-Qusour, calling for the fall of the president.
In the town of Taibat Al-Imam a large nighttime demonstration were held
accompanied by the tunes of: it is time for you, Bashar, to take off and
leave. Nighttime demonstrations were held also in Kernaz and Kafr Zita. The
activists in the city of Souran and Taibat Al-Imam distributed- to all the
shops- pamphlets calling for the [national] strike.
- 7:00 p.m.: A huge explosion in the area between the towns of Khan Shikhoun
and Al-Habit, the explosion was executed by the Free Syrian Army and caused
much damage to the regimes forces.
- 8:00 p.m.: Firing from the checkpoints-barricades in Kafr Zita in
retaliation after a nighttime demonstration was held by locals.
- 8:30 p.m.: Electricity was cut off from the northern part of the
neighborhood of Al-Hamidiya. Huge security reinforcements arriving to the
neighborhood from the close by areas of Duwar Al-Bahra (the bonds
roundabout) and Al-Arbaeen (the 40s) neighborhood.  Also large numbers of
Shabiha (regime-sponsored gangs), with weapons and gear, arrived at Al-Assad
medical Plaza.
- 11:15 p.m.: Heavy gunfire in Sahl Al-Ghab by Al-Assad gangs, a 7 years old
child was injured. A tank with 12 Shabiha in it roamed Kafr Zita terrorizing
the people.
And in Al-Hadir gunfire was heard.
- 12:00 a.m.: The neighborhood of Al-Baroudiya was stormed by security
forces and Shabiha. In Kafr Zita a warplane flew over the city.
